WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.000
[grim music plays]

2
00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:12.000
[man 1] The time is 13:45 hours

3
00:00:12.080 --> 00:00:17.120
on Wednesday. the 30th of December.

4
00:00:17.200 --> 00:00:19.200
[grim music continues]

5
00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:26.280
You've been arrested
on suspicion of Section 3 RTA 1988.

6
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:28.280
[Caroline] My mum was going. "Any update?"

7
00:00:28.360 --> 00:00:29.520
None.

8
00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:32.680
So we were just literally
both sitting in the kitchen

9
00:00:32.760 --> 00:00:35.720
watching my mobile phone and house phone.
waiting for the police to call.

10
00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:37.600
[grim music continues]

11
00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:39.640
[man 2] As Procurator
Fiscal Head of Homicide.

12
00:00:39.720 --> 00:00:43.000
I had knowledge of every murder
and suspicious death

13
00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:45.120
that occurred across Scotland.

14
00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:49.720
A huge amount of resource was put in
to try to find Tony Parsons.

15
00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:53.960
and there was not
a single trace of him anywhere.

16
00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:58.160
Dr. Muirhead coming forward was the first
lead the police had had in years.

17
00:00:59.200 --> 00:01:02.200
So I instructed the police
to arrest the McKellar brothers.

18
00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:05.600
[officer] Armed police! Stand still!

19
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:06.840
[grim music continues]

20
00:01:06.920 --> 00:01:09.280
[Caroline] People started to privately
message me on Facebook

21
00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:12.280
saying. "My gosh.
what happened to the boys? Are they okay?"

22
00:01:12.360 --> 00:01:13.920
[officer] Show your hands!
On the ground!

23
00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.360
[Caroline] The boys were taken
by officers in balaclavas

24
00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:18.320
to the police station for questioning.

25
00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:19.240
[man 1] Your name?

26
00:01:19.320 --> 00:01:21.360
Alexander Gardner McKellar.

27
00:01:22.080 --> 00:01:23.720
[man 1] What's your age?

28
00:01:23.800 --> 00:01:24.640
Twenty-nine.

29
00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:26.560
I was thinking. "It's still not too late."

30
00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:29.320
"If you go and confess.
you can do the right thing.

31
00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:31.120
and this ordeal would be over."

32
00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:33.120
[man 1] What is it you do? Self-employed?

33
00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:36.040
Farmer. Anything to do
with the farm. really.

34
00:01:36.120 --> 00:01:36.960
[man 1] Okay.

35
00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:39.080
You didn't show that man any kindness
at the time.

36
00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:40.800
but you can show kindness now.

37
00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:43.160
It might be late.
but it's better late than never.

38
00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:45.520
[man 1] You'll be asked
about your involvement in offenses

39
00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:48.040
under Section 3A
of the Road Traffic Act 1988.

40
00:01:48.120 --> 00:01:50.400
That is causing the death of another

41
00:01:50.480 --> 00:01:53.960
using a vehicle
whilst unfit through drink or drugs.

42
00:01:54.040 --> 00:01:58.640
We understand that he's told Dr. Muirhead
precisely what has happened.

43
00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:01.680
So. potentially.
potentially he might tell the police.

44
00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:03.680
[man 1] You're not bound to answer.
but if you do.

45
00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:05.360
your answers will be recorded.

46
00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:08.080
may be noted and may be used
in evidence. understand?

47
00:02:08.160 --> 00:02:09.000
Yeah.

48
00:02:10.560 --> 00:02:13.560
[Caroline] Two detectives arrived
at my parents' front door.

49
00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:16.800
They said. "We need to sit down
and have a conversation."

50
00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:19.080
[grim music continues]

51
00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:22.160
I had this horrible feeling
in my stomach that this has gone wrong.

52
00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:26.000
[man 1] Have you ever been involved
in a road accident involving a cyclist?

53
00:02:26.080 --> 00:02:27.320
No comment.

54
00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:30.200
[man 1] Have you been involved
in a crime and tried to cover it up?

55
00:02:30.280 --> 00:02:31.920
No comment.

56
00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:34.200
[man 1] Can you tell me
what you were doing

57
00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:38.480
on Friday. the 29th of September. 2017?

58
00:02:38.560 --> 00:02:39.600
No comment.

59
00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:43.600
Caroline Muirhead told us Sandy said
he'd knocked Mr. Parsons down

60
00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:45.280
and that he was buried on the estate.

61
00:02:45.880 --> 00:02:48.080
[man 1] Do you know
where Anthony Parsons is?

62
00:02:49.320 --> 00:02:53.880
[David] But until the body of Tony Parsons
is found and then recovered.

63
00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:56.560
there is nothing whatsoever to show

64
00:02:56.640 --> 00:02:58.640
that that was a truthful statement.

65
00:02:58.720 --> 00:03:00.520
[man 1] Did you see
Anthony Parsons at all?

66
00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:01.960
No comment.

67
00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:04.000
[man 1] Were you the last person
to see him alive?

68
00:03:04.080 --> 00:03:05.240
No comment.

69
00:03:05.320 --> 00:03:08.760
There was no basis
at that time to charge them.

70
00:03:08.840 --> 00:03:10.440
[grim music continues]

71
00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:13.960
The detective said. "We didn't have enough
to hold them. we had to release them."

72
00:03:15.600 --> 00:03:17.840
And my brain's just going.

73
00:03:18.640 --> 00:03:19.480
"Fuck."

74
00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:21.120
[grim music continues]

75
00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:23.840
Then she went. "Don't worry.
we maintained your anonymity."

76
00:03:23.920 --> 00:03:26.560
And I was like.
"Who else do they think it's gonna be?"

77
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:27.840
[grim music continues]

78
00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:31.040
"We seized the estate.
so the boys won't be allowed back there."

79
00:03:31.120 --> 00:03:32.440
I said. "Where will they go?"

80
00:03:33.040 --> 00:03:35.120
"That's none of your concern. Caroline."

81
00:03:35.200 --> 00:03:37.640
It is when he's obviously
gonna get in touch with me.

82
00:03:37.720 --> 00:03:40.240
If you've just released him.
he's gonna get in touch.

83
00:03:40.320 --> 00:03:43.560
"Well. you tell him that
you've just heard that he's been arrested.

84
00:03:43.640 --> 00:03:46.800
and you've got your job.
and you don't wanna deal with him."

85
00:03:46.880 --> 00:03:49.720
That's not gonna fly.
I've told this guy I wanna marry him.

86
00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:51.640
"What if he turns up
at my parents' house?"

87
00:03:51.720 --> 00:03:54.240
"You call the police."
Well. then it's a bit too late. isn't it?

88
00:03:55.200 --> 00:03:57.760
[David] Witness protection
is all about a risk assessment

89
00:03:57.840 --> 00:04:01.800
of the level of threat
that the individual poses.

90
00:04:01.880 --> 00:04:03.960
This isn't a serious
and organized crime group

91
00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:07.080
who are about to go
and shoot other rivals.

92
00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:08.440
[grim music continues]

93
00:04:08.520 --> 00:04:11.800
The police advised Dr. Muirhead
to stay with her parents.

94
00:04:11.880 --> 00:04:15.920
to call them if she had
any contact from the McKellar brothers.

95
00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:22.480
They plainly felt that that was sufficient
in the circumstances to ensure her safety.

96
00:04:23.640 --> 00:04:26.120
Caroline said.
"You've gotta get alarms for the house."

97
00:04:26.200 --> 00:04:28.640
"You've gotta get door locks.
you've gotta get window locks."

98
00:04:28.720 --> 00:04:30.400
And she was totally panicking.

99
00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:31.520
She was frightened.

100
00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:33.160
[grim music continues]

101
00:04:33.240 --> 00:04:36.280
[Caroline] What's to stop him
turning up at my mum and dad's front door?

102
00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:39.000
What is he thinking?

103
00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:40.400
Does he think this was me?

104
00:04:40.480 --> 00:04:42.440
What have the police said to him?

105
00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:44.200
[grim music swells]

106
00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:45.400
Would he harm me?

107
00:04:47.640 --> 00:04:51.520
This man was trained
to kill professionally.

108
00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:54.280
And so I felt fucking terrified.

109
00:04:58.520 --> 00:05:00.600
[grim music fades out]

110
00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:02.680
[dramatic string music plays]

111
00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:09.920
[David] The police were told
by Dr. Muirhead she left a Red Bull can

112
00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:13.320
at the spot that
Sandy McKellar said he'd buried the body.

113
00:05:14.600 --> 00:05:17.640
So we followed
the directions provided by Dr. Muirhead.

114
00:05:18.280 --> 00:05:22.440
You drive down
into the estate onto a rough track.

115
00:05:22.920 --> 00:05:25.840
crossing a ford and up into a hilly area.

116
00:05:25.920 --> 00:05:27.760
It's exceptionally remote.

117
00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:31.200
We were being kept abreast of matters
as they were happening.

118
00:05:31.280 --> 00:05:32.360
[shutters click]

119
00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:37.360
The first thing the police did
was to go search the area

120
00:05:37.440 --> 00:05:39.400
to see whether there was a Red Bull can.

121
00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:41.200
And lo and behold. there was.

122
00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:43.280
[dramatic string music continues]

123
00:05:50.240 --> 00:05:54.920
If the body of Tony Parsons isn't
underneath or near to the Red Bull can…

124
00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:56.400
[shutters click]

125
00:05:57.240 --> 00:06:00.920
…the chances of us finding it
are negligible to zero.

126
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.440
You couldn't possibly search
the whole estate.

127
00:06:03.520 --> 00:06:05.520
If we don't find the body.
there is no case.

128
00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:09.680
There's no basis upon which the McKellars
can be re-arrested and re-questioned.

129
00:06:09.760 --> 00:06:11.720
[dramatic string music continues]

130
00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:15.560
I said to my mum I was gonna go stay
at a friend's. but I lied.

131
00:06:18.400 --> 00:06:21.600
I didn't want to put them in danger
or put them to any harm.

132
00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:23.880
[dramatic string music continues]

133
00:06:24.640 --> 00:06:27.160
I went back to my flat
'cause I just wanted to be on my own.

134
00:06:28.360 --> 00:06:30.880
When I arrived back.
there was a parcel waiting for me.

135
00:06:30.960 --> 00:06:32.600
[dramatic string music continues]

136
00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:34.560
And I knew it was gonna be one thing.

137
00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:40.640
Inside the box was the wedding dress
that his mum and I had ordered online.

138
00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:42.280
there in all its glory.

139
00:06:43.320 --> 00:06:44.960
I thought. "Do you know what?"

140
00:06:46.040 --> 00:06:47.440
"Fuck it. let's wear it."

141
00:06:47.520 --> 00:06:49.520
["Clair de Lune" plays]

142
00:06:50.480 --> 00:06:52.480
[chuckles. sniffles]

143
00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:54.680
[exhales]

144
00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:58.600
Too big.

145
00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:03.040
Heh. [sucks teeth]

146
00:07:05.760 --> 00:07:06.600
Oh. well.

147
00:07:06.680 --> 00:07:08.080
And I was just spiraling.

148
00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:11.320
And I think in my. sort of.

149
00:07:12.120 --> 00:07:13.640
pathetic way.

150
00:07:13.720 --> 00:07:15.840
I wanted to see
what it would've felt like…

151
00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:18.520
to wear it.

152
00:07:18.600 --> 00:07:19.880
Stupid as that sounds.

153
00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:21.960
["Clair de Lune" continues]

154
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:27.520
You kind of have those moments
where you think. you know.

155
00:07:27.600 --> 00:07:30.080
"I wonder.
if this was an alternate timeline.

156
00:07:30.160 --> 00:07:33.280
what may have been
and what could've happened."

157
00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:36.560
You know it's not your reality.
but you like to daydream

158
00:07:36.640 --> 00:07:38.880
because just for those few minutes.

159
00:07:38.960 --> 00:07:41.160
it just takes you to a nicer.
happier place.

160
00:07:41.240 --> 00:07:43.240
["Clair de Lune" continues]

161
00:07:48.040 --> 00:07:49.960
[grim music plays]

162
00:07:50.040 --> 00:07:50.880
[mobile phone chimes]

163
00:07:50.960 --> 00:07:53.880
Suddenly. I get a message
pop up in my inbox

164
00:07:55.800 --> 00:07:57.920
from Robert and Sandy's friend.

165
00:07:58.000 --> 00:07:58.960
Click on it…

166
00:07:59.640 --> 00:08:03.600
And the message says. "Hi. Caroline.
Robert and Sandy are with me."

167
00:08:03.680 --> 00:08:06.880
"They've come to stay with me
and my family an hour from Glasgow."

168
00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:11.240
They've seen that I've read the messages.
"Fuck. fuck. fuck. shit."

169
00:08:11.320 --> 00:08:14.400
They were clearly on their phone
the same time I was on my phone.

170
00:08:14.480 --> 00:08:16.520
[grim music continues]

171
00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:18.760
And they're waiting on you to reply.

172
00:08:18.840 --> 00:08:20.600
If I don't answer
that message immediately.

173
00:08:21.200 --> 00:08:23.560
and immediately say.
"I miss you. I love you."

174
00:08:23.640 --> 00:08:26.720
it'd be so obvious
that I'd been the one to betray him.

175
00:08:26.800 --> 00:08:28.800
[grim music continues]

176
00:08:38.840 --> 00:08:41.160
[Caroline] Before I knew it.
the phone is ringing.

177
00:08:41.240 --> 00:08:45.160
And they'll know
that the phone is in my hand ringing.

178
00:08:45.240 --> 00:08:47.240
You have to answer it.

179
00:08:47.320 --> 00:08:48.680
You just go.

180
00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:50.720
"Fuck."

181
00:08:50.800 --> 00:08:51.680
"Hi."

182
00:08:51.760 --> 00:08:53.920
[grim music continues]

183
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:58.280
I said. "I got messages from your friends
saying that you've been arrested."

184
00:08:58.360 --> 00:08:59.880
"What the hell is going on?"

185
00:08:59.960 --> 00:09:03.000
"Caroline. I've been trying to reach you.
I'm so worried about you."

186
00:09:03.080 --> 00:09:04.120
[grim music continues]

187
00:09:04.200 --> 00:09:07.000
He went. "I think we've been
under surveillance for ages."

188
00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:11.040
"Robert's definitely opened
his stupid mouth when he's been drinking."

189
00:09:11.120 --> 00:09:15.200
"But. end of the day. Robert and I said.
'No comment' to everything. so it's fine."

190
00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:18.600
So I'm actually getting
this sense of hope. in some ways.

191
00:09:18.680 --> 00:09:21.040
that maybe the police kept me anonymous.

192
00:09:21.120 --> 00:09:23.160
[grim music continues]

193
00:09:23.240 --> 00:09:26.360
Unless he's playing
a really. really dark. twisted game here.

194
00:09:26.440 --> 00:09:29.000
he can't know that
it was me who went to the police.

195
00:09:29.680 --> 00:09:32.360
And he was like.
"You've got your flat in Glasgow."

196
00:09:32.440 --> 00:09:35.240
And he was like. "When can we head over?"

197
00:09:35.320 --> 00:09:37.920
I'd resigned myself
to never hear from him again.

198
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:41.400
My brain was…
in these two conflicting worlds.

199
00:09:41.480 --> 00:09:43.960
I missed him.
I wanted to see if he was okay.

200
00:09:44.040 --> 00:09:45.960
But also. inviting him over to my flat

201
00:09:46.040 --> 00:09:49.440
means I'm putting myself
in a really precarious situation.

202
00:09:49.520 --> 00:09:51.080
[grim music continues]

203
00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:53.160
But as mental as it sounds.

204
00:09:53.840 --> 00:09:55.160
I said yes.

205
00:09:55.640 --> 00:09:56.600
[telephone rings]

206
00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:59.200
-[anxious music plays]
-[Caroline's footsteps]

207
00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:03.240
[Caroline breathes deeply]

208
00:10:03.320 --> 00:10:04.160
[door buzzes]

209
00:10:07.320 --> 00:10:09.120
You're standing
behind the door thinking.

210
00:10:09.200 --> 00:10:11.400
"This is either the best way to be safe

211
00:10:11.480 --> 00:10:13.400
or the most stupid thing
you've ever done."

212
00:10:13.480 --> 00:10:17.160
"And the most recklessly dangerous thing
you've ever done."

213
00:10:18.680 --> 00:10:22.320
You've got these big six-foot men
walking up a wee small corridor.

214
00:10:22.400 --> 00:10:24.480
looming into the viewfinder.

215
00:10:28.840 --> 00:10:31.360
I remember thinking. "Look happy."

216
00:10:31.440 --> 00:10:33.800
"Because you are happy to see them.

217
00:10:33.880 --> 00:10:38.920
because they were just arrested. released.
so you'll be so happy they weren't held.

218
00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:40.040
so relieved."

219
00:10:40.120 --> 00:10:44.280
"Embrace them. be warm with them.
laugh with them. comfort them."

220
00:10:44.360 --> 00:10:45.760
"'Cause otherwise. you're fucked."

221
00:10:45.840 --> 00:10:47.840
[anxious music continues]

222
00:10:51.160 --> 00:10:52.680
Body language tells you a lot.

223
00:10:52.760 --> 00:10:55.440
And he just seemed
genuinely relieved to see me.

224
00:10:55.520 --> 00:10:56.880
[anxious music continues]

225
00:10:59.480 --> 00:11:00.840
In that moment.

226
00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:03.520
I felt the heat was off.

227
00:11:03.600 --> 00:11:05.280
So you're thinking.

228
00:11:06.720 --> 00:11:09.560
"Good. this is okay.
this is fine. this is not bad."

229
00:11:10.240 --> 00:11:12.000
But then you're also thinking.

230
00:11:12.080 --> 00:11:13.640
"I need to be clever about this

231
00:11:13.720 --> 00:11:16.680
and create a plan in my own head
of how to survive this."

232
00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:19.760
[anxious music swells]

233
00:11:22.440 --> 00:11:24.520
[anxious music crescendos]

234
00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:25.840
[club music plays]

235
00:11:25.920 --> 00:11:28.040
[Caroline] I needed to keep them
in good spirits

236
00:11:28.120 --> 00:11:30.480
as much as I possibly could
until they found the body.

237
00:11:30.560 --> 00:11:33.720
Right. music on.
pass the drink. pass the cigarette.

238
00:11:33.800 --> 00:11:34.880
let's have a party.

239
00:11:35.600 --> 00:11:37.360
We used substances and we drank.

240
00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:40.720
and drugs and alcohol
let you be a separate. different person.

241
00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:42.600
[club music continues]

242
00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:45.120
All the while.
they have no idea that I'm the one

243
00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:48.000
who instigated that entire police arrest.

244
00:11:48.520 --> 00:11:50.480
You're literally living
on the knife's edge.

245
00:11:51.560 --> 00:11:53.560
I don't know
how long this is going to take.

246
00:11:53.640 --> 00:11:57.760
and I'm starting to panic
that maybe Sandy actually got it wrong.

247
00:11:57.840 --> 00:11:59.960
And what if he isn't there?

248
00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:03.200
What if they're searching
and maybe they don't find him?

249
00:12:04.320 --> 00:12:06.800
Please. God. let the body be there.

250
00:12:06.880 --> 00:12:08.880
[intriguing music plays]

251
00:12:14.640 --> 00:12:19.640
[woman] I got a phone call from the senior
investigating officer in this case.

252
00:12:19.720 --> 00:12:24.520
They'd got some witness information
that they might know

253
00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:28.320
where the missing cyclist. Mr. Parsons.
might be located.

254
00:12:28.400 --> 00:12:30.280
[intriguing music continues]

255
00:12:30.360 --> 00:12:31.880
And I was asked. could I go along

256
00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:35.280
to see if there were any clues
from the soil or the vegetation

257
00:12:35.360 --> 00:12:37.680
that might support this witness statement?

258
00:12:37.760 --> 00:12:41.280
[reporter] Cancer survivor. Tony Parsons.
had been crossing Scotland

259
00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:44.000
in a 100-mile charity cycle.

260
00:12:44.080 --> 00:12:47.800
[Lorna] Everyone remembered on the news.
just a few years previously.

261
00:12:47.880 --> 00:12:53.360
Mr. Parsons had been on a charity cycle
from Fort William to Tillicoultry.

262
00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:55.600
and he just vanished without a trace.

263
00:12:55.680 --> 00:12:58.080
[reporter] Here in September 2017.

264
00:12:58.160 --> 00:13:01.360
the Navy veteran was captured on CCTV

265
00:13:01.440 --> 00:13:03.440
weaving through the rural roads.

266
00:13:03.520 --> 00:13:06.080
[shutter clicks]

267
00:13:07.080 --> 00:13:09.200
[Lorna] As we walked over the area.

268
00:13:09.280 --> 00:13:13.080
I could see that there was
an area that was devoid of vegetation.

269
00:13:13.160 --> 00:13:15.280
[intriguing music continues]

270
00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:18.240
What we were finding
was that the older peat.

271
00:13:18.320 --> 00:13:19.840
the amorphous. mushy peat.

272
00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:22.360
was actually very near the surface.

273
00:13:22.440 --> 00:13:25.800
and so this area
had indeed been recently dug up.

274
00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:27.800
[intriguing music continues]

275
00:13:27.880 --> 00:13:31.320
This was the place
where Mr. Parsons might be.

276
00:13:31.400 --> 00:13:33.080
[intriguing music continues]

277
00:13:33.160 --> 00:13:36.440
So at that stage.
the forensic team has to be put together.

278
00:13:36.520 --> 00:13:38.400
[shutter clicks]

279
00:13:38.480 --> 00:13:42.880
So that would involve
an appropriately skilled digger driver.

280
00:13:42.960 --> 00:13:45.480
skilled forensic archaeologists.

281
00:13:45.560 --> 00:13:47.640
the forensic anthropologists.

282
00:13:47.720 --> 00:13:49.200
[shutter clicks]

283
00:13:49.280 --> 00:13:52.440
[David] An exhumation isn't something
that happens quickly.

284
00:13:52.520 --> 00:13:57.440
You have to do it
in a very controlled. measured way.

285
00:13:57.520 --> 00:14:00.080
just as an archaeologist would do
in an ancient site.

286
00:14:00.160 --> 00:14:01.600
[intriguing music continues]

287
00:14:01.680 --> 00:14:04.280
The Auch Estate is extremely remote.

288
00:14:04.360 --> 00:14:06.280
and it was the depths of winter.

289
00:14:06.360 --> 00:14:09.240
so it was plainly something
that was going to take a period of time.

290
00:14:09.320 --> 00:14:11.600
[intriguing music continues]

291
00:14:11.680 --> 00:14:14.480
[Caroline] The days are going by.
waiting for that man to be found.

292
00:14:15.440 --> 00:14:19.800
It was so cold that the canal had frozen
outside my front window.

293
00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:22.800
so everyone was trying to stay indoors
and keep warm.

294
00:14:22.880 --> 00:14:24.160
[intriguing music continues]

295
00:14:24.240 --> 00:14:27.240
You're living with killers.
sleeping alongside killers.

296
00:14:27.320 --> 00:14:31.880
You're having dinner alongside killers.
Killers who think you're on their side.

297
00:14:31.960 --> 00:14:33.440
And you've betrayed them.

298
00:14:33.520 --> 00:14:37.000
[reporter] Searches for a cyclist
who went missing more than three years ago

299
00:14:37.080 --> 00:14:38.840
are continuing in the Highlands.

300
00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:42.440
[Caroline] Their fear was also palpable
about what was gonna happen to them.

301
00:14:42.520 --> 00:14:44.280
Everything's on high alert.

302
00:14:44.360 --> 00:14:46.440
[reporter] Police say
their investigation continues.

303
00:14:46.520 --> 00:14:50.640
and are once again urging
anyone with information to come forward.

304
00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:53.120
[Caroline] Their phone beeped.
you'd jump out your skin.

305
00:14:53.200 --> 00:14:56.560
I didn't know if a message would come
that said. "It was Caroline."

306
00:14:56.640 --> 00:14:57.600
It was exhausting.

307
00:14:57.680 --> 00:15:00.520
[menacing music plays]

308
00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:03.400
At one point. Robert signaled to me
that he wanted to have a chat.

309
00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:06.640
I'm thinking.
"What the hell is this gonna be about?"

310
00:15:06.720 --> 00:15:11.120
He looked so sad
and. like. empty. you know?

311
00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:13.200
[menacing music continues]

312
00:15:18.360 --> 00:15:21.280
He said. "Caroline.
I don't know what Sandy's told you."

313
00:15:25.840 --> 00:15:28.520
"But you have to understand.
when we hit that man…

314
00:15:28.600 --> 00:15:30.240
[menacing music continues]

315
00:15:30.320 --> 00:15:32.120
…it happened very fast.

316
00:15:32.200 --> 00:15:34.040
and he flew over the car."

317
00:15:35.320 --> 00:15:39.000
"We got out.
and when we walked towards him.

318
00:15:39.080 --> 00:15:40.320
he was alive."

319
00:15:41.600 --> 00:15:43.840
I thought he had been killed on impact.

320
00:15:44.520 --> 00:15:45.480
Fuck.

321
00:15:45.560 --> 00:15:47.920
[menacing music continues]

322
00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:48.960
[exhales]

323
00:15:50.440 --> 00:15:54.440
He was saying it as if.
like. unburdening yourself.

324
00:15:55.440 --> 00:16:00.080
And Robert said that he moved him
to the side of the road with the bike.

325
00:16:00.160 --> 00:16:02.360
so they could change vehicles
and come back.

326
00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:06.920
And I was like. "Robert. so you left him
alone on the side of the road?"

327
00:16:07.800 --> 00:16:09.400
He was like. "Of course we did."

328
00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:16.200
And the thought
of that man being in agony.

329
00:16:16.280 --> 00:16:18.720
and you hide them from any passing car

330
00:16:18.800 --> 00:16:21.400
that may come down
that could help them or save them.

331
00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:25.520
that is a cruelty to another
which was so needless.

332
00:16:25.600 --> 00:16:28.160
[menacing music continues]

333
00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:30.960
If you'd called an ambulance.
and he passed away before it arrived.

334
00:16:31.040 --> 00:16:32.480
at least you've tried.

335
00:16:32.560 --> 00:16:35.120
[menacing music continues]

336
00:16:35.200 --> 00:16:37.400
He said. "We went back.

337
00:16:37.480 --> 00:16:38.720
changed cars.

338
00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:40.440
left our SIM cards…

339
00:16:42.800 --> 00:16:44.520
changed our clothes.

340
00:16:46.520 --> 00:16:47.760
put gloves on."

341
00:16:49.840 --> 00:16:50.840
"We went back.

342
00:16:50.920 --> 00:16:52.840
and he was still alive.

343
00:16:52.920 --> 00:16:55.440
but weakening. fading."

344
00:16:56.360 --> 00:16:59.440
They carefully lifted him into a tarpaulin
and then drove him back.

345
00:16:59.520 --> 00:17:02.000
and they kept him
overnight in a wooded area.

346
00:17:02.080 --> 00:17:05.520
And then that same vehicle was used
by the hunting clients the next day.

347
00:17:06.360 --> 00:17:08.360
[menacing music continues]

348
00:17:15.040 --> 00:17:18.200
Then they buried Tony Parsons
once the clients had left.

349
00:17:19.080 --> 00:17:21.000
And so whether it was an accident or not.

350
00:17:21.080 --> 00:17:25.040
all your actions. then. after it
are not accidental.

351
00:17:25.120 --> 00:17:28.960
And they're quite methodical.
and they're well planned out.

352
00:17:29.040 --> 00:17:33.400
And in my head.
this wasn't. then. a hit-and-run.

353
00:17:34.440 --> 00:17:36.040
This was…

354
00:17:36.120 --> 00:17:37.960
potentially a murder.

355
00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:40.040
[dramatic music plays]

356
00:17:41.680 --> 00:17:42.920
Later that night.

357
00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:44.240
Sandy's sitting there.

358
00:17:44.320 --> 00:17:47.360
and he's starting to talk away.
having a cigarette.

359
00:17:47.440 --> 00:17:50.240
clearly in his memories.
and he's pondering things.

360
00:17:50.320 --> 00:17:54.000
and he's being quite open about the case.

361
00:17:54.080 --> 00:17:56.320
[dramatic music continues]

362
00:17:56.400 --> 00:17:57.760
It occurred to me that

363
00:17:57.840 --> 00:18:00.400
if I was able to record
some of the stuff Sandy was saying.

364
00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:02.320
I would be able to help the police.

365
00:18:02.400 --> 00:18:04.840
and I might be able
to even record a confession.

366
00:18:04.920 --> 00:18:06.160
[dramatic music continues]

367
00:18:06.240 --> 00:18:08.520
So that it could be over and finished.

368
00:18:09.560 --> 00:18:14.080
I've got my chess website out. playing.
and to the left it said. "Voice recorder."

369
00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:17.000
He would have zero idea
if I just clicked that record button.

370
00:18:17.080 --> 00:18:19.320
[dramatic music continues]

371
00:18:19.400 --> 00:18:22.440
I'm playing the chess game
whilst it's recording in the background.

372
00:18:25.880 --> 00:18:28.640
What I find slightly weird
with you. Sandy. is. like.

373
00:18:28.720 --> 00:18:33.600
in some ways. you're so compassionate.
so loving. so friendly. so gentle.

374
00:18:34.200 --> 00:18:35.480
I can't imagine it.

375
00:18:36.640 --> 00:18:40.040
But then when I see you
when you've been drinking and stuff.

376
00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:41.960
I can see you guys doing it.

377
00:18:43.080 --> 00:18:44.440
[Sandy] I don't know.

378
00:18:44.520 --> 00:18:46.760
I don't know about anything anymore.

379
00:18:46.840 --> 00:18:48.840
[Caroline] It was a huge risk.

380
00:18:48.920 --> 00:18:51.080
Any point. he could've come
and put his arm around you

381
00:18:51.160 --> 00:18:52.840
and been like. "How's your game going?"

382
00:18:53.560 --> 00:18:55.600
[Sandy] The fact that
they're still questioning folk.

383
00:18:55.680 --> 00:18:58.120
and they're still trying
to divvy off everybody…

384
00:18:59.520 --> 00:19:01.200
It's not a clear-cut case.

385
00:19:02.840 --> 00:19:05.760
[Caroline] The thing that I think
you're going to get into trouble for…

386
00:19:07.800 --> 00:19:09.640
is the lack of empathy.

387
00:19:12.520 --> 00:19:14.080
[Sandy] Fucking hell. it's warm in here.

388
00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:19.040
[Caroline] I was starting to think.
"This won't work. This is going nowhere."

389
00:19:19.120 --> 00:19:21.440
So I tried to be more confrontational.

390
00:19:21.520 --> 00:19:24.400
How could you go out hunting
the next day and not be bothered?

391
00:19:25.600 --> 00:19:27.040
Like you must have been.

392
00:19:28.960 --> 00:19:30.480
[Sandy exhales]

393
00:19:30.560 --> 00:19:32.360
[Caroline] How could you not be. though?

394
00:19:35.880 --> 00:19:37.800
[Sandy] It was either my life or his.

395
00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:43.600
[Caroline] My brain went.
"You've got it on recording.

396
00:19:43.680 --> 00:19:45.040
but stop now."

397
00:19:45.120 --> 00:19:47.120
[dramatic music continues]

398
00:19:49.080 --> 00:19:50.560
I saw him walking over and I think.

399
00:19:50.640 --> 00:19:54.200
"This is now. potentially.
really not a safe situation."

400
00:19:57.680 --> 00:19:59.200
[phone rings]

401
00:19:59.280 --> 00:20:00.640
[dramatic music fades out]

402
00:20:00.720 --> 00:20:01.800
[Caroline] Can you get that?

403
00:20:01.880 --> 00:20:04.480
-[Sandy] What is it?
-[Caroline] It's my Deliveroo.

404
00:20:05.800 --> 00:20:07.600
I've got Red Bull and some cans.

405
00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:10.520
Healthy diet. yeah?

406
00:20:16.280 --> 00:20:18.360
When someone says.
"It's my life or theirs."

407
00:20:18.840 --> 00:20:23.160
it was the admission I was so relieved
I had the voice recorder on for.

408
00:20:23.240 --> 00:20:26.240
But equally you're thinking.
"But then why is he not saying.

409
00:20:26.320 --> 00:20:29.920
'And I regret it.' or. 'I'm upset by it.'
or. 'I think about it'?"

410
00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:31.120
[grim music plays]

411
00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:34.320
Was he actually someone
who cared that he'd done this?

412
00:20:34.800 --> 00:20:37.120
The extremes of the kindness
and the cruelty

413
00:20:37.200 --> 00:20:39.560
that both these twin boys had shown

414
00:20:39.640 --> 00:20:41.120
made me really wonder.

415
00:20:41.200 --> 00:20:45.600
what could have possibly happened
in their lifetime to make them that way?

416
00:20:45.680 --> 00:20:47.680
[grim music continues]

417
00:20:51.040 --> 00:20:56.880
[man] From 1999 to 2011.
I was a community police officer

418
00:20:57.840 --> 00:21:01.720
responsible for 79 square miles
of Argyll and Bute.

419
00:21:02.720 --> 00:21:06.600
It was community policing
in its original sense.

420
00:21:06.680 --> 00:21:11.080
back in the old days. you know.
the cop responsible for an area.

421
00:21:11.160 --> 00:21:12.400
And I fell in love with it.

422
00:21:13.800 --> 00:21:15.240
I had left the police.

423
00:21:15.320 --> 00:21:17.880
and I was aware of a missing person case.

424
00:21:17.960 --> 00:21:20.320
I think I was watching a local news story.

425
00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:24.560
and one mentioned the Bridge of Orchy.
and I'm like. "Well. that's my beat."

426
00:21:24.640 --> 00:21:27.000
[reporter] Tony Parsons
was cycling from Fort William

427
00:21:27.080 --> 00:21:28.960
back to his hometown of Tillicoultry

428
00:21:29.040 --> 00:21:30.200
when he went missing.

429
00:21:30.280 --> 00:21:32.040
[Greg] So I'm interested.

430
00:21:32.120 --> 00:21:35.680
So I'm like. "Whoa. Stop. rewind. play.
What've we got here?"

431
00:21:36.400 --> 00:21:38.400
[reporter] Police arrested
two 29-year-old men

432
00:21:38.480 --> 00:21:40.960
in connection
with Mr. Parsons' disappearance.

433
00:21:41.040 --> 00:21:43.480
They were released
pending further inquiries.

434
00:21:43.560 --> 00:21:45.120
"Oh! They've arrested somebody."

435
00:21:45.200 --> 00:21:47.840
"That's good.
Arrested two people. Interesting."

436
00:21:47.920 --> 00:21:50.720
"I wonder who that is.
I wonder if it's who I think it is."

437
00:21:50.800 --> 00:21:52.200
[dramatic music plays]

438
00:21:52.280 --> 00:21:55.240
I knew the McKellar brothers as boys.

439
00:21:56.720 --> 00:21:58.880
I would spend a lot of time
in the schools.

440
00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:01.880
Community policing.
stranger danger. cycling proficiency…

441
00:22:01.960 --> 00:22:04.040
I'd like to think
I meant something to them.

442
00:22:04.120 --> 00:22:07.560
I've certainly got the pictures
I think Robert drew of me. you know?

443
00:22:07.640 --> 00:22:10.960
I kept it. I had it on my office wall.
I've still got it. I'll show you.

444
00:22:12.360 --> 00:22:13.880
They were rough and ready.

445
00:22:13.960 --> 00:22:16.920
And I remember
having discussions in the school

446
00:22:17.600 --> 00:22:19.880
about maybe what the boys
were exposed to at home.

447
00:22:19.960 --> 00:22:22.440
It was enough
for the teacher to be concerned.

448
00:22:22.520 --> 00:22:26.480
I felt that that influence on the boys
came from the father.

449
00:22:26.560 --> 00:22:28.240
Tom McKellar.

450
00:22:29.440 --> 00:22:31.360
There was a couple of serious allegations.

451
00:22:31.440 --> 00:22:35.080
And the intelligence was enough for us
to get a warrant to search Auch Estate.

452
00:22:35.160 --> 00:22:38.520
And we found firearms
throughout the house.

453
00:22:38.600 --> 00:22:40.560
[dark music plays]

454
00:22:40.640 --> 00:22:41.680
[clicking]

455
00:22:41.760 --> 00:22:42.960
We found pistols.

456
00:22:43.040 --> 00:22:44.920
Now. pistols are illegal to own.

457
00:22:45.000 --> 00:22:47.920
And we found a firearm
within Sandy's bedroom.

458
00:22:48.000 --> 00:22:50.000
[dark music continues]

459
00:22:50.080 --> 00:22:52.120
Having firearms strewed about your house.

460
00:22:52.200 --> 00:22:54.520
lying about
in your primary school kid's bedroom.

461
00:22:54.600 --> 00:22:55.960
this is serious now.

462
00:22:56.040 --> 00:22:59.000
And that resulted
in Tom McKellar getting prosecuted.

463
00:23:00.960 --> 00:23:02.240
From the age of 7.

464
00:23:02.320 --> 00:23:04.120
the familiarity with firearms…

465
00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:06.200
-[fires shot]
-[Sandy] Holy shit!

466
00:23:06.280 --> 00:23:08.120
[dark music continues]

467
00:23:08.200 --> 00:23:11.960
…the slaughtering of animals
and the disposal of animals…

468
00:23:12.040 --> 00:23:15.360
There seemed to be an acceptance
of that at too young an age.

469
00:23:16.240 --> 00:23:18.480
If you're exposed to it day and daily.

470
00:23:18.560 --> 00:23:21.960
it's gonna desensitize you
to taking a life.

471
00:23:22.040 --> 00:23:23.320
[dark music continues]

472
00:23:23.400 --> 00:23:26.120
My thought at the time
when I was watching that newsreel was.

473
00:23:26.200 --> 00:23:29.640
"It is a good place to conceal a person."

474
00:23:29.720 --> 00:23:33.160
There's still bodies missing
here in Argyll that we haven't found.

475
00:23:33.240 --> 00:23:35.240
[dark music plays]

476
00:23:39.400 --> 00:23:43.040
[Lorna] The priority
was to take each zone.

477
00:23:43.120 --> 00:23:47.680
each layer of the soil.
centimeter by centimeter.

478
00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:50.480
Peat is dark.

479
00:23:50.560 --> 00:23:52.360
It's very dark brown.

480
00:23:52.440 --> 00:23:56.040
It's also. near the surface.
quite fibrous.

481
00:23:56.120 --> 00:23:57.840
So it hides things in it.

482
00:23:58.720 --> 00:24:02.760
We were looking for material
that had come from human origins.

483
00:24:02.840 --> 00:24:08.120
such as hair. fingernails.
any human-introduced material.

484
00:24:11.440 --> 00:24:14.640
When the archaeologists got further down.

485
00:24:15.240 --> 00:24:17.280
there were bones appearing.

486
00:24:17.760 --> 00:24:20.800
And what the anthropologists said was.

487
00:24:20.880 --> 00:24:23.640
"These look like deer bones."

488
00:24:24.400 --> 00:24:25.920
[flash snaps]

489
00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:28.560
[shutter clicks]

490
00:24:28.640 --> 00:24:33.320
And what it turned out to be
was what is called a… a kill pit.

491
00:24:33.960 --> 00:24:39.000
Gamekeepers on that estate.
the McKellars. would have used this area

492
00:24:39.080 --> 00:24:42.360
to dispose of parts of the animals
that were not required.

493
00:24:42.440 --> 00:24:45.120
[dark music continues]

494
00:24:45.200 --> 00:24:47.640
There had to be
a veterinary surgeon brought along

495
00:24:47.720 --> 00:24:51.000
to confirm that these were.
indeed. relatively fresh.

496
00:24:51.080 --> 00:24:54.120
These were consistent
with having been put in

497
00:24:54.200 --> 00:24:57.240
from the same time
that Mr. Parsons disappeared.

498
00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:04.800
But also. we were seeing an awful lot
of these little bits of wood chip.

499
00:25:05.800 --> 00:25:09.000
You wouldn't find wood chippings there.
It's not natural.

500
00:25:09.080 --> 00:25:11.920
They wouldn't be there
unless they'd been introduced.

501
00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:14.680
The question is. where did they come from?

502
00:25:15.160 --> 00:25:19.320
So we drove down
to the Auch Estate farmyard.

503
00:25:19.400 --> 00:25:21.400
[mysterious music plays]

504
00:25:23.600 --> 00:25:27.000
As we were walking through that.
we saw a digger truck.

505
00:25:28.840 --> 00:25:31.600
When we looked at the bucket. within it.

506
00:25:32.360 --> 00:25:33.720
there was these wood chips.

507
00:25:39.440 --> 00:25:41.320
Those chippings were the same

508
00:25:41.400 --> 00:25:44.720
as the wood chips
that were found at the scene.

509
00:25:46.840 --> 00:25:48.720
What was particularly significant

510
00:25:48.800 --> 00:25:53.240
was the dimensions
between the teeth on the bucket.

511
00:25:53.320 --> 00:25:55.960
It was the same dimensions
that were measured

512
00:25:56.040 --> 00:25:59.440
between the marks
that were left at the peat bog.

513
00:25:59.520 --> 00:26:00.760
[flashbulb pops]

514
00:26:00.840 --> 00:26:05.440
But only a few people would have
access to that particular vehicle.

515
00:26:05.520 --> 00:26:08.920
And two of those people
were the McKellar twins.

516
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:10.480
[mysterious music continues]

517
00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:14.160
[David] We can trace the evidence
at the kill pit back to Robert and Sandy.

518
00:26:14.240 --> 00:26:18.240
but it's not enough to prove their guilt
because we had not found the body yet.

519
00:26:21.920 --> 00:26:25.280
[intriguing music plays]

520
00:26:26.200 --> 00:26:27.720
[Caroline] Every day going past.

521
00:26:27.800 --> 00:26:30.360
I'm thinking.
"Surely they've got him by now."

522
00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:33.200
I have not heard
anything from the police. so…

523
00:26:33.840 --> 00:26:37.520
I was so at a loss
as to what was happening.

524
00:26:37.600 --> 00:26:39.280
[intriguing music continues]

525
00:26:39.360 --> 00:26:44.360
And I felt like
I was in a state of permanent fear.

526
00:26:44.440 --> 00:26:46.560
And I'm lying in bed.
and I'm tossing and turning.

527
00:26:46.640 --> 00:26:49.160
[intriguing music continues]

528
00:26:49.240 --> 00:26:50.960
And Sandy's snoring beside me.

529
00:26:51.040 --> 00:26:53.080
And then there was just this pounding.

530
00:26:53.160 --> 00:26:54.840
[knocking at door]

531
00:26:54.920 --> 00:26:57.680
Like bang. bang. bang on the front door.

532
00:27:00.680 --> 00:27:01.960
"Shit! Shit! Fuck! Fuck!"

533
00:27:02.040 --> 00:27:04.640
I'm thinking. "The only people
who do that is the police."

534
00:27:04.720 --> 00:27:06.720
[knocking continues]

535
00:27:07.440 --> 00:27:08.880
I'm like. jump out of the bed.

536
00:27:08.960 --> 00:27:10.840
close my bedroom door as fast as I can.

537
00:27:10.920 --> 00:27:13.920
And I go down the… go down my hall.

538
00:27:14.720 --> 00:27:18.800
There is the same female detective
who had been at my parents' house.

539
00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:22.680
Open the door ever so slightly.

540
00:27:22.760 --> 00:27:26.080
I'm like… [whispers]
"Can I speak to you downstairs?"

541
00:27:26.160 --> 00:27:27.440
[tense music plays]

542
00:27:27.520 --> 00:27:28.640
"Who do you have in there?"

543
00:27:28.720 --> 00:27:31.560
"I need to speak to you
in the car. outside."

544
00:27:31.640 --> 00:27:32.840
"Why?"

545
00:27:32.920 --> 00:27:33.760
"Who's in there?"

546
00:27:35.200 --> 00:27:36.280
"Friends."

547
00:27:36.360 --> 00:27:37.200
"You're lying."

548
00:27:37.280 --> 00:27:38.600
Bang.

549
00:27:38.680 --> 00:27:41.680
[tense music continues]

550
00:27:41.760 --> 00:27:45.360
And she opens up the door
where Robert was sleeping.

551
00:27:45.440 --> 00:27:48.840
She goes. "What the fuck. Caroline?!
You're our witness."

552
00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:51.360
And I'm thinking. "Did he hear that?"

553
00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:54.720
And the man goes in
and grabs Robert from the bed.

554
00:27:54.800 --> 00:27:58.480
She's storming into the bedroom
at the top. grabbing Sandy out of the bed.

555
00:27:59.040 --> 00:28:00.880
And they go.
"You're not supposed to be here.

556
00:28:00.960 --> 00:28:03.080
you're supposed to be
in care of friends in Aberfoyle."

557
00:28:03.160 --> 00:28:06.960
And Sandy goes. "I'm allowed to stay here.
This is my partner's house."

558
00:28:07.040 --> 00:28:10.120
I'm going. "Of course you're allowed
to stay here. Sandy. if you want to."

559
00:28:11.400 --> 00:28:15.960
And they went. "Right. you two.
you need to be out of here ASAP."

560
00:28:18.640 --> 00:28:20.040
And like that. they left.

561
00:28:22.480 --> 00:28:25.920
The police were checking on Caroline
to see if she was safe.

562
00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:27.400
I have no doubt they were astonished

563
00:28:27.480 --> 00:28:30.240
to discover the McKellars
were with her in the flat.

564
00:28:30.320 --> 00:28:32.600
Had she cut all contact with them.

565
00:28:32.680 --> 00:28:34.680
which she could readily have done.

566
00:28:35.160 --> 00:28:39.680
then. plainly.
she would have been rather safer.

567
00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:43.320
Personally. I'd have run a mile
to the nearest police station.

568
00:28:43.400 --> 00:28:46.320
and then I'd have kept on going
to a place of safety.

569
00:28:46.400 --> 00:28:48.760
and I would not have seen him again.

570
00:28:48.840 --> 00:28:50.840
[mysterious music plays]

571
00:28:53.280 --> 00:28:56.320
[Caroline] I'm standing in my living room.
and Robert goes…

572
00:28:58.560 --> 00:29:00.080
"Caroline.

573
00:29:00.160 --> 00:29:01.760
how did she know your name?"

574
00:29:01.840 --> 00:29:03.840
[grim music plays]

575
00:29:04.840 --> 00:29:07.720
"Have you met her before?
Does she know you?"

576
00:29:08.200 --> 00:29:10.160
"Have you spoken to the police?"

577
00:29:12.440 --> 00:29:13.800
"No. no. No. no. no. no."

578
00:29:13.880 --> 00:29:17.000
And Sandy. thankfully.
intervened and went. "Robert. back off."

579
00:29:17.080 --> 00:29:19.160
"Caroline would not do that to us."

580
00:29:19.240 --> 00:29:21.720
"She loves us. I trust her."

581
00:29:22.480 --> 00:29:25.040
And I could see. like.
Robert was so angry.

582
00:29:25.120 --> 00:29:27.800
Sandy's comforting Robert.
and they're hugging each other.

583
00:29:27.880 --> 00:29:29.320
Robert's like. "What'll we do?"

584
00:29:29.400 --> 00:29:31.480
[grim music continues]

585
00:29:31.560 --> 00:29:35.680
Sandy's like. "Look. Robert.
it was three years ago."

586
00:29:37.800 --> 00:29:40.120
"If they had anything.
they'd have got us by now."

587
00:29:40.200 --> 00:29:42.040
"They're not gonna find him."

588
00:29:42.120 --> 00:29:44.080
"Even if they could
dig up that entire place.

589
00:29:44.160 --> 00:29:45.240
they're not gonna find him."

590
00:29:45.320 --> 00:29:47.880
[grim music continues]

591
00:29:47.960 --> 00:29:50.760
Robert was like.
"Right. we need to get out of here now."

592
00:29:50.840 --> 00:29:52.680
And Sandy's then like.

593
00:29:52.760 --> 00:29:55.080
"I'm legally allowed
to stay with my fiancée."

594
00:29:55.160 --> 00:29:56.640
"They can't argue with that."

595
00:29:58.240 --> 00:30:01.880
Robert leaves to stay
with family friends outside of Glasgow.

596
00:30:01.960 --> 00:30:04.080
and Sandy and I are then left in the flat.

597
00:30:05.200 --> 00:30:09.120
He's like. "No. Caroline.
I know you would never. ever betray me."

598
00:30:09.200 --> 00:30:11.680
The way Sandy was defending me was so…

599
00:30:13.400 --> 00:30:15.240
weirdly comforting. [cries]

600
00:30:17.600 --> 00:30:19.160
To survive in that moment.

601
00:30:19.240 --> 00:30:22.120
I genuinely started to believe my own lie.

602
00:30:22.200 --> 00:30:24.080
[grim music continues]

603
00:30:24.160 --> 00:30:26.000
I was the supportive girlfriend there.

604
00:30:26.080 --> 00:30:28.280
who'd also been treated badly
by the police.

605
00:30:30.560 --> 00:30:31.760
I was lying.

606
00:30:31.840 --> 00:30:35.480
I was betraying.
Yes. it was for a really good reason.

607
00:30:35.560 --> 00:30:38.440
But lying erodes a part of your soul.

608
00:30:38.520 --> 00:30:43.120
It was such a toxic entanglement.

609
00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:44.720
[grim music continues]

610
00:30:44.800 --> 00:30:48.000
[Margaret] Caroline said.
"Mum. he thinks we're still a couple."

611
00:30:48.080 --> 00:30:50.520
"What do I do? He has a key."

612
00:30:51.520 --> 00:30:53.800
I know that she was very. very afraid.

613
00:30:53.880 --> 00:30:56.760
And she would lie there thinking.

614
00:30:56.840 --> 00:30:58.440
"How do I get out of this?"

615
00:30:58.520 --> 00:30:59.800
[grim music continues]

616
00:30:59.880 --> 00:31:02.600
I honestly thought
I was going to have a heart attack.

617
00:31:02.680 --> 00:31:04.200
Was he gonna hurt her?

618
00:31:04.280 --> 00:31:05.760
Would-- would he kill her?

619
00:31:05.840 --> 00:31:07.840
[grim music continues]

620
00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:11.800
[Caroline] The police had said.
"You cannot tell anyone about this."

621
00:31:11.880 --> 00:31:14.560
"Otherwise. you could compromise
this entire investigation."

622
00:31:14.640 --> 00:31:16.600
[grim music continues]

623
00:31:16.680 --> 00:31:19.960
But I needed to talk to someone about it.

624
00:31:20.040 --> 00:31:23.440
The next opportunity when Sandy left.
I reached out to someone

625
00:31:23.520 --> 00:31:26.480
who wouldn't judge me for the state
I was in and would understand.

626
00:31:26.560 --> 00:31:28.920
[melancholy music plays]

627
00:31:29.000 --> 00:31:31.720
[James] "You may have noticed
I've been unusually quiet of late."

628
00:31:34.040 --> 00:31:37.560
"Don't know how I've managed it.
but I've been witness to a crime."

629
00:31:38.040 --> 00:31:41.200
"I can even hear you in my head
saying. 'Oh my days.'"

630
00:31:42.080 --> 00:31:46.520
And so I decided
to drive to her flat to see her.

631
00:31:46.600 --> 00:31:51.200
And she opened the door.
and she looked absolutely shocking.

632
00:31:51.280 --> 00:31:54.200
I was like.
"What the hell has happened here?"

633
00:31:54.280 --> 00:31:56.680
[melancholy music continues]

634
00:31:56.760 --> 00:32:00.800
Caroline is like anally clean.
OCD-level clean.

635
00:32:00.880 --> 00:32:03.320
And this house was disgusting.

636
00:32:04.320 --> 00:32:07.840
She was just word-vomiting
this information at me

637
00:32:07.920 --> 00:32:09.800
in no coherent structure or order.

638
00:32:09.880 --> 00:32:12.760
It took me about 20 minutes to work out
what she was trying to tell me.

639
00:32:12.840 --> 00:32:14.960
[melancholy music continues]

640
00:32:15.040 --> 00:32:18.280
Sandy had been involved
in the death of this guy.

641
00:32:19.200 --> 00:32:22.880
She's now spying on Sandy.

642
00:32:22.960 --> 00:32:25.720
Sandy. who we've just found out
has murdered somebody.

643
00:32:25.800 --> 00:32:28.160
was living in the flat.
which I didn't know.

644
00:32:28.240 --> 00:32:32.000
and had actually just popped out
for some beers

645
00:32:32.080 --> 00:32:33.240
and was coming back.

646
00:32:33.320 --> 00:32:35.320
[melancholy music continues]

647
00:32:36.640 --> 00:32:40.000
And I was like.
"What the fuck is going on here?"

648
00:32:40.080 --> 00:32:41.600
And my wife's heavily pregnant.

649
00:32:41.680 --> 00:32:44.400
and I just need to…
I need to leave the situation.

650
00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:48.240
And as I was leaving.
Sandy just arrived back.

651
00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:52.000
He put out. uh. like. a hand
to shake his hand.

652
00:32:52.080 --> 00:32:54.560
And I just kind of
awkwardly shook his hand

653
00:32:54.640 --> 00:32:58.240
and said. "Nice to meet you."
and then walked straight away.

654
00:32:58.320 --> 00:33:00.320
[melancholy music turns dramatic]

655
00:33:01.320 --> 00:33:02.800
I was devastated.

656
00:33:03.760 --> 00:33:05.760
Her life was falling to pieces.

657
00:33:05.840 --> 00:33:09.960
And I think it's one of the few times
I've cried in about the last 20 years.

658
00:33:10.040 --> 00:33:12.120
I just-- It was all too much.

659
00:33:13.560 --> 00:33:16.000
[Caroline] I'll be honest.
I was so manic at that point.

660
00:33:16.080 --> 00:33:19.720
I don't really think I had
any control over what I was doing.

661
00:33:19.800 --> 00:33:23.120
I think. in some ways.
my life was becoming so surreal.

662
00:33:23.200 --> 00:33:24.840
my grasp on reality was weakening.

663
00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:27.040
[dark music plays]

664
00:33:27.120 --> 00:33:29.960
[reporter] Police have been scouring
this estate near Bridge of Orchy

665
00:33:30.040 --> 00:33:31.520
for around two weeks.

666
00:33:31.600 --> 00:33:33.920
It's understood specialist search officers

667
00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:36.760
and forensic teams
are excavating the area.

668
00:33:36.840 --> 00:33:38.680
[dark music continues]

669
00:33:38.760 --> 00:33:40.880
[Caroline] Sandy gets a message
from a friend

670
00:33:40.960 --> 00:33:44.080
that said the police
are looking at the carcass pits.

671
00:33:44.160 --> 00:33:46.920
We've been. I don't know.
listening to music or something.

672
00:33:47.000 --> 00:33:48.320
and he just slammed the radio off.

673
00:33:48.400 --> 00:33:52.320
and he just started smashing his fists
off the sideboard.

674
00:33:53.280 --> 00:33:56.040
Being like. "How do they know?
How do they know?"

675
00:33:56.120 --> 00:33:59.280
"Fuck! Fuck!
How do they know where he is?"

676
00:33:59.360 --> 00:34:01.640
[dark music continues]

677
00:34:01.720 --> 00:34:04.000
I said. "You're fine.
They don't know where he is."

678
00:34:04.080 --> 00:34:06.600
And he was like.
"How could they be in that area?"

679
00:34:06.680 --> 00:34:07.840
"The place is so huge."

680
00:34:07.920 --> 00:34:11.360
I was like. "Someone else must know.
or someone on the farm told them."

681
00:34:11.440 --> 00:34:13.920
[dark music continues]

682
00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:18.240
He had warped into. like. a crazed mania.

683
00:34:18.320 --> 00:34:20.200
He was convinced there were spy devices

684
00:34:20.280 --> 00:34:22.880
or taps for the police
to listen to the flat.

685
00:34:24.160 --> 00:34:28.000
And he gutted the-- I mean.
every light fitting. everything.

686
00:34:28.680 --> 00:34:31.000
essentially starting to trash it.

687
00:34:32.600 --> 00:34:34.560
There was just this inhuman desire

688
00:34:34.640 --> 00:34:36.960
to try and find
whatever device the police left.

689
00:34:38.760 --> 00:34:41.560
I was just thinking.
"I've told the police where he is."

690
00:34:41.640 --> 00:34:43.600
"I've marked the site

691
00:34:43.680 --> 00:34:45.960
to make this as fast as possible
for you guys."

692
00:34:46.040 --> 00:34:48.040
"This can't take forever."

693
00:34:48.120 --> 00:34:50.920
But it felt like absolute forever.

694
00:34:51.000 --> 00:34:53.000
[melancholy string music plays]

695
00:34:54.440 --> 00:34:57.320
[Lorna] It was a Thursday in January.

696
00:34:57.800 --> 00:34:59.800
It was a cold. cold day.

697
00:35:00.800 --> 00:35:03.480
It was a day that I'll remember
for the rest of my life.

698
00:35:07.880 --> 00:35:12.840
We were digging down
to about 30. 35 centimeters.

699
00:35:13.760 --> 00:35:16.680
And the forensic archaeologist

700
00:35:17.480 --> 00:35:21.120
took her trowel
and carefully was removing down.

701
00:35:21.200 --> 00:35:23.400
millimeter by millimeter.

702
00:35:23.480 --> 00:35:24.440
And she said.

703
00:35:25.280 --> 00:35:28.520
"There's something red here.
There's red material here."

704
00:35:28.600 --> 00:35:30.600
[melancholy string music continues]

705
00:35:32.400 --> 00:35:34.040
And we could see that

706
00:35:34.800 --> 00:35:38.200
it looked like fabric
that Mr. Parsons was last seen wearing

707
00:35:38.280 --> 00:35:39.880
when he was cycling his bike.

708
00:35:39.960 --> 00:35:41.600
[melancholy string music continues]

709
00:35:44.920 --> 00:35:49.440
And you could see that there were
the fingerless gloves of a cyclist.

710
00:35:49.520 --> 00:35:55.400
And indeed. she discovered that
there was a ring on his wedding finger.

711
00:35:58.400 --> 00:36:01.960
He was lifted onto the stretcher.

712
00:36:02.040 --> 00:36:05.440
and… as he was carried out.

713
00:36:05.520 --> 00:36:08.440
the sun came out between the clouds.

714
00:36:09.720 --> 00:36:13.680
We all stood with our heads bowed.

715
00:36:13.760 --> 00:36:16.360
[melancholy string music turns poignant]

716
00:36:17.560 --> 00:36:20.680
And we all said a little silent prayer

717
00:36:21.840 --> 00:36:24.440
for Mr. Parsons and his family.

718
00:36:24.520 --> 00:36:27.560
I think not knowing what has happened

719
00:36:28.240 --> 00:36:30.320
to your loved one is…

720
00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:33.120
Is a form of torture. really.

721
00:36:33.200 --> 00:36:37.120
To be able to bring that.
at least. to an end

722
00:36:37.200 --> 00:36:39.760
by saying. "We have recovered his body."

723
00:36:39.840 --> 00:36:41.400
"We will. in the fullness of time.

724
00:36:41.480 --> 00:36:44.880
give you back the body
to allow you to have a funeral."

725
00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:47.720
gives them something to hold on to.

726
00:36:50.760 --> 00:36:52.760
[string music fades out]

727
00:36:52.840 --> 00:36:56.760
Now. human remains have been found
in a remote part of Argyll.

728
00:36:56.840 --> 00:37:00.040
Police have been carrying out
extensive searches in the area

729
00:37:00.120 --> 00:37:01.560
as part of their investigation

730
00:37:01.640 --> 00:37:04.640
into the disappearance
of cyclist Tony Parsons.

731
00:37:04.720 --> 00:37:07.640
The 63-year-old was last seen
more than three years ago.

732
00:37:07.720 --> 00:37:09.600
Sasha Spratt reports.

733
00:37:09.680 --> 00:37:11.000
[electronic music plays]

734
00:37:11.080 --> 00:37:14.160
[Caroline] The news broke out
to say human remains had been found

735
00:37:14.240 --> 00:37:15.080
on the Auch Estate.

736
00:37:16.800 --> 00:37:18.800
Sandy sat down.

737
00:37:18.880 --> 00:37:22.320
and I'm expecting
him to scream and shout or kick off.

738
00:37:22.400 --> 00:37:25.440
and he actually just sat in silence
for quite a while.

739
00:37:25.520 --> 00:37:29.040
I think. in that moment.
he was a bit broken.

740
00:37:29.680 --> 00:37:31.360
But he had this idea or this notion

741
00:37:31.440 --> 00:37:34.520
that perhaps there'd been
another farmworker on the estate

742
00:37:34.600 --> 00:37:37.160
who maybe had seen something
or who had leaked something.

743
00:37:37.240 --> 00:37:40.240
And he. thankfully.
never thought at any moment

744
00:37:40.320 --> 00:37:43.000
that. you know. one. it'd be me.

745
00:37:43.080 --> 00:37:45.640
or two. that there'd been.
like. an actual marker.

746
00:37:45.720 --> 00:37:47.840
[electronic music continues]

747
00:37:47.920 --> 00:37:51.000
Sandy and his brother
were allowed to return to the estate.

748
00:37:52.040 --> 00:37:54.960
So I dropped him home
and waved him goodbye.

749
00:37:56.000 --> 00:37:59.520
It was a mix of heartbreak
and genuine relief.

750
00:38:00.240 --> 00:38:02.480
I drove as fast as I could
to the police station

751
00:38:02.560 --> 00:38:05.760
because Robert had told me
Tony Parsons was potentially still alive

752
00:38:05.840 --> 00:38:07.200
at the time of the accident.

753
00:38:07.280 --> 00:38:11.000
and I also had
a confession of sorts on my laptop.

754
00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:12.840
and I wanted the police to hear it.

755
00:38:14.120 --> 00:38:16.000
[electronic music continues]

756
00:38:19.680 --> 00:38:22.920
[Caroline] How could you go out hunting
the next day and not be bothered?

757
00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:24.920
[Sandy] It was either my life or his.

758
00:38:26.640 --> 00:38:29.000
[electronic music continues]

759
00:38:30.000 --> 00:38:31.800
[Caroline] I remember messaging
my mum and dad.

760
00:38:31.880 --> 00:38:34.160
They were like. "We're so proud of you."

761
00:38:34.240 --> 00:38:36.880
It was like. "Oh!"

762
00:38:36.960 --> 00:38:40.080
I was like.
"I've done some good in the world."

763
00:38:40.840 --> 00:38:43.560
[David] Dr. Muirhead had provided
the police with information

764
00:38:43.640 --> 00:38:46.440
that Robert McKellar had confirmed to her

765
00:38:46.520 --> 00:38:52.080
that Tony Parsons was alive at the time
they removed him to the estate.

766
00:38:52.960 --> 00:38:54.600
That information changed it

767
00:38:54.680 --> 00:38:56.960
because it altered what we were looking at

768
00:38:57.040 --> 00:39:00.760
from a potential charge
of causing death by dangerous driving

769
00:39:00.840 --> 00:39:03.280
into the most serious crime it could be.

770
00:39:03.360 --> 00:39:04.440
namely one of murder.

771
00:39:04.520 --> 00:39:06.160
[electronic music continues]

772
00:39:06.240 --> 00:39:09.520
But in Scotland.
we have what's known as corroboration.

773
00:39:09.600 --> 00:39:14.920
So that all relevant facts
must be proved by two sources of evidence.

774
00:39:15.000 --> 00:39:17.040
[electronic music continues]

775
00:39:17.120 --> 00:39:21.600
Mr. Parsons' body would not be capable
of being examined immediately

776
00:39:21.680 --> 00:39:23.960
because of the fact it was frozen.

777
00:39:24.040 --> 00:39:27.800
There's a delay of seven days or so
before it can be examined.

778
00:39:29.280 --> 00:39:32.920
So until a full postmortem
has been conducted

779
00:39:33.000 --> 00:39:37.720
and the pathologists have come
to a conclusion as to the cause of death.

780
00:39:37.800 --> 00:39:41.920
and in this case. very particularly.
whether that death was instantaneous.

781
00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:45.640
there's still no basis to arrest them

782
00:39:45.720 --> 00:39:49.280
because we don't know
what the appropriate charges might be.

783
00:39:49.360 --> 00:39:51.360
[pulsing music plays]

784
00:39:54.200 --> 00:39:56.120
[Caroline] Arriving back at my flat.

785
00:39:56.200 --> 00:40:00.720
for the first time in. like. two weeks
I didn't feel manic or frenetic.

786
00:40:00.800 --> 00:40:04.320
And the sun was shining. it was starting
to feel lighter and happier.

787
00:40:04.400 --> 00:40:06.400
[phone buzzes]

788
00:40:07.720 --> 00:40:09.720
[Caroline breathes deeply]

789
00:40:10.440 --> 00:40:12.720
And my phone rings. and it's Sandy.

790
00:40:13.800 --> 00:40:15.640
I can hear he's driving the pickup truck.

791
00:40:15.720 --> 00:40:17.360
He's on the loudspeaker.

792
00:40:17.440 --> 00:40:19.560
And. you know. I was like. "Hi."

793
00:40:20.240 --> 00:40:22.000
He was screaming.

794
00:40:22.080 --> 00:40:26.480
"You fucking little bitch.
you fucking did this!"

795
00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:28.120
I said. "I've not done anything."

796
00:40:28.200 --> 00:40:29.680
[pulsing music continues]

797
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:32.680
He said that Police Scotland
used a local farming lad

798
00:40:32.760 --> 00:40:34.800
to help with the grave-digging.

799
00:40:34.880 --> 00:40:37.080
"There was
a sugar-free Red Bull can left there."

800
00:40:37.160 --> 00:40:40.880
"You're the only person who drinks
sugar-free Red Bull. so you left it."

801
00:40:40.960 --> 00:40:42.560
[pulsing music continues]

802
00:40:42.640 --> 00:40:45.520
And he's just like. "You fucking did this.

803
00:40:45.600 --> 00:40:47.200
and I have defended you to everyone."

804
00:40:47.280 --> 00:40:50.160
"I said it wasn't you.
and you fucking did this!"

805
00:40:50.240 --> 00:40:54.200
"You've handed me in. You've fucked me
and Robert over. You've fucked our lives."

806
00:40:54.280 --> 00:40:58.440
He was like. "I need to see you right now.
and we need to do this face-to-face."

807
00:40:58.520 --> 00:41:01.640
And he hangs up the phone.
and I swear to God. I started screaming.

808
00:41:01.720 --> 00:41:03.200
[pulsing music continues]

809
00:41:03.280 --> 00:41:06.520
My brain was like.
"You are going to get extremely hurt now."

810
00:41:06.600 --> 00:41:08.480
[pulsing music continues]

811
00:41:08.560 --> 00:41:11.040
He's got the spare keys to my flat
on the car keys.

812
00:41:11.520 --> 00:41:14.480
And I was like.
"I'm gonna die. He is going to kill me."

813
00:41:14.560 --> 00:41:16.560
[pulsing music swells]

814
00:41:18.520 --> 00:41:20.680
[dramatic string music plays]

815
00:42:07.360 --> 00:42:09.520
[dramatic string music fades out]
